            <h2>DEFINITION</h2>
            <P class="content">Robotics is the intersection of science, engineering and technology that produces machines, called robots, that
            replicate or substitute for human actions. Robots perform basic and repetitive tasks with greater efficiency and
            accuracy than humans, making them ideal for industries like manufacturing. However, the introduction of artificial
            intelligence in robotics has given robots the ability to handle increasingly complex situations in various industries.
</P><br><br>

